Class GPThread

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • GP.GP.GPThread
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable

    public final class GPThread
extends Thread
    The GPThread class handles the fitness function calculation for a subset of the population as defined by the population size / number of threads.

      • GPThread

        public GPThread(ArrayList<com.github.javaparser.ast.CompilationUnit> population,
                String gpThreadName,
                String programPath,
                String buggyProgramPath)
        The constructor for the GPThread class, ensures that the public field variables; population, gpThreadName, programPath and buggyProgramPath are set.
        Parameters:
        population - An ArrayList of Compilation Units representing a mutation of the original buggy Defects4j program
        gpThreadName - The unique thread number used to represent part of the program path
        programPath - The program path represents the path on the file system where the Defects4j bug has been checked out
        buggyProgramPath - The path to the buggy program path, is a combination of the program path and buggy program path fields
